But the way 60 Minutes structured it, they made it seem like detransitioning is a SIGNIFICANT problem. They interviewed twice as many detransitioners as they did actual trans people. (5/6)
The thing is, 5% of those who detransitioned said that they did so because they realized transitioning "wasn't for them." This makes up 0.4% of the sample. (4/6)

HOWEVER, 62% of those who detransitioned said they were not, at the time of the survey, living as their AGAB.

The most common reason for detransitioning was parental pressure (36%). A large chunk of respondents reported detransitioning due to outside pressure. (3/6)

They said that there is no statistic on detransitioners. There is.

The 2015 US Transgender Survey (USTS, N = 27,715) asked about detransitioning. They found that 8% had detransitioned at some point. (2/6)
